Add Phase 1 tools: get_balance, get_geo_list, get_price, change_geo, buy_proxy

All five remaining MVP tools land at once, with shared resolvers in the API
client:

- resolveCountryId(ISO|number) via cached get_id_country (1h TTL)
- resolveOperatorName(string) via cached get_operators_list (1h TTL)
- getGeoList() via cached get_geo_list (5min TTL)
- invalidateProxyCaches() called after change_geo / buy_proxy

Tools:
- get_balance: zero-arg wrapper over {status, balance, can_payout}
- get_geo_list: client-side ISO filter, no other params; cached
- get_price: accepts ISO or numeric id_country, sorts by period asc
- change_geo: change_equipment with ISO/numeric/geoid/operator resolution,
  check_after_change defaults true
- buy_proxy: destructiveHint=true, idempotentHint=false, estimate_only flag
  for dry-runs, period_days validated against [1,3,7,14,30,60,90,180,365]

Live smoke run (scripts/smoke.mjs) exercises all 6 non-destructive tools
against mobileproxy.space and passes; change_geo + buy_proxy are skipped
unless explicitly opted into (would cost money / trigger hardware swaps).

Types: BalanceResponse, CountryEntry, GeoEntry, OperatorEntry, PriceEntry,
ChangeEquipmentResponse, BuyProxyResponse - all reflecting the actual
response shapes (raw arrays where applicable, Stringish for PHP-string
numeric fields, no fictional envelope).

README updated with the full 8-tool catalogue.

